'''Youssef Belammari''' (Arabic: يُوسُف بَلْعُمَرِيّ; born 20 September 1998) is a Moroccan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[Egyptian Premier League]] club [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

He began his football career by joining the youth teams of [[Fath Union Sport]]s when he was aged 10. In 2017, he was called-up to the first team but he did not fully establish himself until the 2019–20 season. In 2023, he signed with [[Raja CA|Raja Club Athletic]] with whom he won the historic invincible-double in the [[2023–24 Raja CA season|2023–24 season]], an unprecedented achievement in the history of Moroccan football.

==Club career==

=== Fath US ===
Born in [[Casablanca]] on 20 September 1998, Youssef Belammari arrived at [[Fath Union Sport]]s's [[youth system]] at a young age. In early 2017, he joined the first team's squad under [[Walid Regragui]].

On 5 April 2017, he made his professional debut against [[Raja CA]] in [[2016–17 Botola]] (2–0 loss).<ref>{{Cite web |title=رسميا: قائمة الفتح الرباطي لمواجهة الرجاء |url=https://www.elbotola.com/article/2017-04-05-12-04-736.html |access-date=2023-08-25 |website=www.elbotola.com |language=Ar}}</ref>

On 28 May, he made his first starting debut against [[MA Tétouan|Moghreb Tetouan]] (1–1 draw). On 27 August 2017, he scored his first professional goal against [[MC Oujda|Mouloudia d'Oujda]] in the first round of the [[2017 Moroccan Throne Cup|2017 Throne Cup]] (1–1 draw).{{citation needed|date=April 2025}}

=== Raja CA ===
On 2 July 2023, he signed a three-year deal with Raja CA and became the club's third summer signing of [[2023–24 Raja CA season|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2023-07-02|date=2023-07-02|language=fr-FR|title=Botola Pro D1 "Inwi": Youssef Belammari signe au Raja Casablanca|url=https://fr.hespress.com/321012-botola-pro-d1-inwi-youssef-belammari-signe-au-raja-casablanca.html|website=Hespress Français - Actualités du Maroc}}<!-- auto-translated by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 27 August 2023, he made his debut with the ''Greens'' against [[Youssoufia Berrechid]] on the opening match of [[2023–24 Raja CA season|the season]] (1–3 win). Slowed down a bit by an ankle injury the he got during a training session, it was against the same opponent on 8 February 2024, that he scored his first goal (2–0 win).<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-10-08 |language=ar |title=الرجاء يفقد خدمات بلعمري أمام اتحاد تواركة بسبب إصابته في التداريب |url=https://m.elbotola.com/article/2023-09-24-09-48-523.html |website=www.elbotola.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web |date=2024-08-02 |title=Botola Pro D1 Inwi: le Raja bat le CAYB et prend les commandes |url=https://sport.le360.ma/botola-pro-1/botola-pro-d1-inwi-le-raja-bat-le-cayb-et-prend-provisoirement-les-commandes-109702 |access-date=2024-08-02 |website=le360.ma |archive-date=8 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240208191311/https://sport.le360.ma/botola-pro-1/botola-pro-d1-inwi-le-raja-bat-le-cayb-et-prend-provisoirement-les-commandes-109702 |url-status=dead }}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 14 June 2024, after a 0–3 win against [[MC Oujda]] in the last round, Raja were crowned champions ending the season without a single defeat – the first team ever to do so in the history of the league and breaking the record of points.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-06-24 |language=fr |title=Raja 2023-2024, plus grand champion de tous les temps |url=https://sport.le360.ma//botola-pro-1/raja-2023-2024-plus-grand-champion-de-tous-les-temps-112523 |website=Le360 Sport}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> On July 1, Raja beat AS FAR once again in the [[2022–23 Moroccan Throne Cup|Throne Cup]] final to secure the third domestic double of its history, and Belammari made a decisive tackle in the final minutes of the match.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-07-07 |language=fr |title=Coupe du Trône: le Raja s'offre l'AS FAR et un beau doublé |url=https://sport.le360.ma//maroc/coupe-du-trone-le-raja-soffre-las-far-et-un-beau-double-112790 |website=Le360 Sport}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

Belammari strongly kicked-off the [[2024–25 Raja CA season|2024–25 season]] with one goal and three assists in the first eight games. The team also qualifies to the [[2024–25 CAF Champions League|Champions League]]'s group stage.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-10-08 |language=ar |title=بلعمري: "نتيجة مباراة الذهاب سهلت علينا المأمورية والجماهير الرجاوية تستحق هذا التأهل" |url=https://m.elbotola.com/article/2024-09-21-22-53-469.html |website=www.elbotola.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-10-08 |date=2024-07-13 |first=عبد الإله |language=ar |last=محب |title=يوسف بلعمري يطمئن جمهور الرجاء |url=https://sport.lesiteinfo.com/elbotola/439776.html |website=لوسيت انفو سبور}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

==International career ==
In October 2017, he received his first call-up to the [[Morocco national under-20 football team|Morocco U20]] squad by [[Mark Wotte]]. He played one friendly game against [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21]] and two other against [[France national under-20 football team|France U20]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=admin |date=2017-10-11 |title=Coupe du monde U20 : Match amical : Italie- Maroc: 4-0 |url=https://mazagan24.com/2017/10/11/coupe-du-monde-u20-match-amical-italie-maroc-4-0/ |access-date=2023-08-25 |website=Mazagan24 - Portail d'El Jadida |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Fédération Française de Football |url=https://www.fff.fr/selection/matchs/167-maroc-france.html |access-date=2023-08-25 |website=www.fff.fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Fédération Française de Football |url=https://www.fff.fr/selection/matchs/707-maroc-france.html |access-date=2023-08-25 |website=www.fff.fr}}</ref> In October 2018, he played two friendly games against [[Algeria national under-23 football team|Algeria]] with the [[Morocco national under-23 football team|Moroccan U23 team]].

In August 2022, Belammari was called up by [[Hussein Ammouta]] to the [[Morocco A' national football team|National A' team]] for a training camp between 1st and 6 August.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Haitami |first=Mohammed |title=منتخب المحليين يدخل معسكرا مغلقا |url=https://sports.lematin.ma/ar/web/2022/34783.html |access-date=2023-08-25 |website=Le Matin Sports}}</ref> The Atlas Lions played a friendly tournament in [[Austria]] against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] and [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Haitami |first=Mohammed |title=الدوري الدولي بالنمسا...المنتخب الوطني يخوض مباراتين فقط |url=https://sports.lematin.ma/ar/web/2022/35124.html |access-date=2023-08-25 |website=Le Matin Sports}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=1970-01-01 |title=تشكيلة المنتخب الوطني للاعبين المحليين أمام قطر – FRMF |url=https://site.frmf.ma/%d8%aa%d8%b4%d9%83%d9%8a%d9%84%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d9%86%d8%aa%d8%ae%d8%a8-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%88%d8%b7%d9%86%d9%8a-%d9%84%d9%84%d8%a7%d8%b9%d8%a8%d9%8a%d9%86-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%ad%d9%84%d9%8a-11/ |access-date=2023-08-25 |language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=1970-01-01 |title=تشكيلة المنتخب الوطني للاعبين المحليين أمام جامايكا – FRMF |url=https://site.frmf.ma/%d8%aa%d8%b4%d9%83%d9%8a%d9%84%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d9%86%d8%aa%d8%ae%d8%a8-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%88%d8%b7%d9%86%d9%8a-%d9%84%d9%84%d8%a7%d8%b9%d8%a8%d9%8a%d9%86-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%ad%d9%84%d9%8a-12/ |access-date=2023-08-25 |language=ar}}</ref>

On 7 October 2024, he received his first call-up with the [[Morocco national football team|first team]] from [[Walid Regragui]], as a reinforcement to replace [[Noussair Mazraoui]], who was out due to injury.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-10-07 |language=fr |last=S.Salimi |title=Football : Regragui convoque Youssef Belammari en renfort après la blessure de Mazraoui |url=https://www.lopinion.ma/Football-Regragui-convoque-Youssef-Belammari-en-renfort-apres-la-blessure-de-Mazraoui_a58720.html |website=L'Opinion Maroc - Actualité et Infos au Maroc et dans le monde.}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web |access-date=2024-10-07 |date=2024-10-07 |language=fr-FR |title=Qualifs CAN 2025: blessé, Noussair Mazraoui remplacé par Youssef Belammari |url=https://www.h24info.ma/qualifs-can-2025-blesse-noussair-mazraoui-remplace-par-youssef-belammari/ |website=24info.ma |archive-date=7 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241107003108/https://www.h24info.ma/qualifs-can-2025-blesse-noussair-mazraoui-remplace-par-youssef-belammari/ |url-status=dead }}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-10-07 |date=2024-10-07 |language=ar |title=يوسف بلعمري يعوض نصير مزراوي المصاب |url=https://www.almountakhab.com/node/16205182 |website=جريدة المنتخب}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> The goal of this gathering is a double confrontation against [[Central African Republic national football team|Central African Republic]], counting for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]s.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-10-03 |date=2024-10-03 |first=Rédaction |language=fr-FR |last=N |title=Maroc-Centrafrique: plusieurs surprises dans la liste de Walid Regragui |url=https://www.lesiteinfo.com/sport/628652-maroc-centrafrique-plusieurs-surprises-dans-la-liste-de-walid-regragui.html |website=LeSiteinfo.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-10-03 |language=fr |title=Lions de l'Atlas: Walid Regragui dévoile sa liste pour la Centrafrique, sans Ziyech |url=https://sport.le360.ma/football/can/lions-de-latlas-walid-regragui-devoile-sa-liste-pour-la-centrafrique-sans-ziyech_I2HW54BF4ZHOTPJV2L6UMFAQ4U/ |website=Le 360 Sport Français}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 23 July 2025, he was announced among the list of players called-up by [[Tarik Sektioui]] to take part in the [[2024 African Nations Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-07-27 |language=fr |title=Tarik Sektioui dévoile sa liste des Lions de l'Atlas pour le CHAN |url=https://sport.le360.ma/football/can/tarik-sektioui-devoile-sa-liste-des-lions-de-latlas-pour-le-chan_GTWRA3AXKNCWBAG5NW2ZXEBGDA/ |website=Le 360 Sport Français}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>  On 28 August 2025, he was included in the squad-list selected to face [[Niger national football team|Niger]] and [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] in the new [[Prince Moulay Abdellah Stadium|Prince Moulay Abdellah stadium]], and qualify to the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-28 |date=2025-08-28 |first=لوماتان |language=ar |last=سبورت |title=استدعاءات جديدة وعودة وجوه شابة في لائحة المنتخب المغربي |url=https://sports.lematin.ma/ar/%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA/%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AF%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%A1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%88%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%88%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%87-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A6%D8%AD%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A/7689 |website=Lematin Sports}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-28 |first=Rabei |language=fr |last=Benkiran |title=La liste de Regragui dévoilée, avec El Karouani et El Aynaoui |url=https://www.lopinion.ma/La-liste-de-Regragui-devoilee-avec-El-Karouani-et-El-Aynaoui_a71159.html |website=L'Opinion Maroc - Actualité et Infos au Maroc et dans le monde.}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> Along with [[El Mehdi Al Harrar]], he was selected while still in [[Nairobi]] to play in the final of the African Nations Championship.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-28 |date=2025-08-28 |language=ar |title=الشان يهدي الحرار مكانا مع الأسود |url=https://www.almountakhab.com/node/13216679 |website=جريدة المنتخب}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 3 August 2025, the ''Atlas Lions'' began the group stage with a victory against [[Angola national football team|Angola]] (2–0).<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-31 |date=2025-08-03 |first=Chady |language=fr-FR |last=Chaabi |title=CHAN 2024. Le Maroc s'offre une première victoire face à l'Angola (2-0) |url=https://medias24.com/2025/08/03/chan-2024-le-maroc-soffre-une-premiere-victoire-face-a-langola-2-0/ |website=Médias24 numéro un de l'information économique marocaine}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> However, they were surprisingly beaten by the host country, [[Kenya national football team|Kenya]], by a score of 1–0.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-31 |first=In a packed Moi International Sports Centre, Kenya pulled off a memorable 1-0 victory over Morocco, two-time tournament champions, to remain unbeaten at the TotalEnergies African Nations Championship (CHAN) |language=en-us |last=PAMOJA 2024 |title=Kenya Defeat Morocco With 10 Men and Edge Closer to CHAN Quarterfinals |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/caf-african-nations-championship/articles/kenya-defeat-morocco-with-10-men-and-edge-closer-to-chan-quarterfinals-2025-08-10 |website=beIN SPORTS}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> In a difficult situation, they bounced back against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] (goals from [[Mohamed Rabie Hrimat|Hrimat]], [[Oussama Lamlioui|Lamlioui]] and [[Sabir Bougrine|Bougrine]]) and the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] (goals from [[Mohamed Rabie Hrimat|Hrimat]] and a brace from [[Oussama Lamlioui|Lamliou]]).<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-31 |language=en-GB |title=Morocco bounce back with 3-1 win, Zambia exit CHAN |url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-african-nations-championship/news/morocco-bounce-back-with-3-1-win-zambia-exit-chan/ |website=Morocco bounce back with 3-1 win, Zambia exit CHAN}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-31 |date=2025-08-17 |first=Chady |language=fr-FR |last=Chaabi |title=CHAN 2024. Le Maroc retrouve la Tanzanie en quart après sa victoire face à la RDC (3-1) |url=https://medias24.com/2025/08/17/chan-2024-le-maroc-retrouve-la-tanzanie-en-quart-apres-sa-victoire-face-a-la-rdc-3-1/ |website=Médias24 numéro un de l'information économique marocaine}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> This success allowed the team to qualify for the quarter-finals where they eliminated the surprise of the tournament, [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]], by the narrowest of margins (1–0), in [[Dar es Salaam]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-31 |language=en-GB |title=Morocco edge Tanzania in Dar to reach CHAN semi-finals |url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-african-nations-championship/news/morocco-edge-tanzania-in-dar-to-reach-chan-semi-finals/ |website=Morocco edge Tanzania in Dar to reach CHAN semi-finals}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> In the semi-finals, the Moroccans faced the defending champions, [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]]. After a hard-fought match that ended 1–1 with a superb goal from [[Sabir Bougrine]], Morocco won on penalties (5–3), thus reaching the final.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-31 |language=en-GB |title=Morocco beat title holders Senegal on penalties to reach CHAN final |url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-african-nations-championship/news/morocco-beat-title-holders-senegal-on-penalties-to-reach-chan-final/ |website=Morocco beat title holders Senegal on penalties to reach CHAN final}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> On August 30, at the [[Nyayo National Stadium]], the ''Atlas Lions'' won the title by beating [[Madagascar national football team|Madagascar]] 3–2, thanks to a brace from [[Oussama Lamlioui]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2025-08-31 |language=en |title=Morocco 3-2 Madagascar (Aug 30, 2025) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/757630/madagascar-morocco |website=ESPN}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 11 December 2025, Belammari was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

